SAVIOR , LIKE A SHEPHERD LEAD US . AND EVERLAST-
1 SAVIOR , like a shepherd lead us ,
Much we need thy tenderest care ;
In thy pleasant pastures feed us ,
For our use thy folds prepare .
1 SAVIOR , like a shepherd lead us , Much we need thy tenderest care ; In thy pleasant pastures feed us , For our use thy folds prepare .
Thou hast bought us , thine we are ;
Thou hast bought us , thine we are .
Blessed Jesus , blessed Jesus , Thou hast bought us , thine we are ; Blessed Jesus , blessed Jesus , Thou hast bought us , thine we are .
2 We are thine , do thou befriend us ,
Be the Guardian of our way ;
Keep thy flock , from sin defend us ,
Seek us when we go astray .
2 We are thine , do thou befriend us , Be the Guardian of our way ; Keep thy flock , from sin defend us , Seek us when we go astray .
Hear young children when they pray .
Blessed Jesus , blessed Jesus , Hear young children when they pray .
3 Thou hast promised to receive us ,
Poor and si iful though we be ;
Thou hast mrercy to relieve us ,
Grace to cleanse , and power to free .
Let us early turn to thee .
3 Thou hast promised to receive us , Poor and si iful though we be ; Thou hast mrercy to relieve us , Grace to cleanse , and power to free . Blesse Jesus , blessed Jesus , Let us early turn to thee .
4 Early let us seek thy favor ,
Early let us do thy will ;
With thy love our bosoms fill .
4 Early let us seek thy favor , Early let us do thy will ; Blessed Lord and only Savior , With thy love our bosoms fill .
Thou hast loved us , love us still .
Blessed Jesus , blessed Jesus , Thou hast loved us , love us still .

He will give you grace to conquer ,

His kingdom spread from shore to shore ,
Till moons shall wax and wane no more .

2 From north to south the princes meet ,
pay their homage at his feet ;
While western empires own their Lord ,
And savage tribes attend his Word .
2 From north to south the princes meet , To pay their homage at his feet ; While western empires own their Lord , And savage tribes attend his Word .

And endless praises crown his head ;
His name , like sweet perfume , shali rise
3 To him shall endless prayer be made , And endless praises crown his head ; His name , like sweet perfume , shali rise With every morning sacrifice .
4 People and realms of every tongue
Dwell on his love with sweetest song ,
Their early blessings on his name .
4 People and realms of every tongue Dwell on his love with sweetest song , And infant voices shall proclaim Their early blessings on his name .
